Section 508 Accessibility master css Accessibility Section 508 Web Alternate Format The Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality is committed to making the information and resources on the Web sites that it sponsors accessible to the widest possible audience including persons with disabilities AHRQ would appreciate being notified of accessibility problems and non compliant Web documents so that we can re mediate them and better serve you Federal agencies are required upon request to provide information and data to individuals with disabilities through an alternative means of access that can be used by the individuals For Alternative Access to Web Documents Contact the Department of Health and Human Services http www hhs gov contacts helpdesk html Help Desk which is staffed by several individuals during business hours and they will assist you or Contact the Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality through the info customer htm Customer Feedback page or by E mail to mailto info ahrq gov info ahrq gov and request an alternate format of the information if you are unable to access the Web site version Synopsis of Section 508 Accessibility Requirements http www section508 gov index cfm FuseAction Content ID 3 Section 508 requires that when Federal agencies develop procure maintain or use electronic and information technology EIT Federal employees with disabilities have comparable access to and use of information and data as Federal employees without disabilities unless an undue burden would be imposed on the agency Section 508 also requires that individuals with disabilities who are members of the public seeking information or services from a Federal agency have comparable access to and use of information and data as the public without disabilities unless an undue burden would be imposed on the agency Although Federal agencies have an explicit statutory obligation to make all EIT that they develop maintain or use compliant with Section 508 the current emphasis is on newly procured EIT because it is the category that is explicitly enforceable by legal action Procurement awards made on or after June 25 2001 are subject to Section 508 Select for http www section508 gov index cfm FuseAction Content ID 13 FAR Final Rule According to the http www access board gov Access Board the Section 508 requirements do not apply retroactively to pre existing EIT Specifically the http www section508 gov index cfm FuseAction Content ID 12 Electronic and Information Technology Accessibility Standards Economic Assessment states that The standards are to be applied prospectively and do not require Federal agencies to retrofit existing electronic and information technology As agencies upgrade and change their electronic and information technology they must comply with the standards It should be noted however that other Federal regulations and guidelines e g http www section508 gov index cfm FuseAction Content ID 17 Section 501 and http www section508 gov index cfm FuseAction Content ID 15 Section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act require equal access for individuals with disabilities Therefore reasonable accommodations will be made to ensure this Last revised June 21 2001 News Information AHRQ Home Page http www hhs gov Department of Health and Human Services 508web htm Accessibility info customer htm Contact Us policyix htm copyright Copyright disclaim htm Disclaimers foia htm FOIA weblink htm Linking privacy htm Privacy Notice
